  "body": "**What happened**:\r\nnode-local-dns caches negative queries, causing things that do polling for orchestration to fail (like operators with StatefulSets).\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nHave a minimal TTL for negative responses (alternatively just disable caching by setting the cache size to 0) that follows what was done for kube-dns: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/53604\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nWith node-local-dns cache deployed, in my cluster it was the https://github.com/coreos/etcd-operator that failed to create clusters because the cached entry didn't expire before it had exhausted all of it's retries.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.11.6\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: GKE\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): any\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): any",
